qMatrix
Class QMatrix<T>

java.lang.Object
  qMatrix.QMatrix<T>

public class QMatrix<T>
extends java.lang.Object

qMatrix is the equivalent of a circularly, doubly linked list, except for matricies. This concept could be confusing, so here is an ascii diagram of what this looks like: Diagram of a sample QMatrix structure: Key: s is the sentinel r is a row sentinel c is a column sentinel q is a node n is the number of columns (not counting sentinel column) m is the number of rows (not counting sentinel row) note that connections wrap to other side | | | | | --s--r--r--r--r-- | | | | | --c--q--q--q--q-- | | | | | --c--q--q--q--q-- | | | | |
